.TH mantis 1  "mantis 0.16.4"
.SH NAME
mantis \- A fast terminal file tree viewer with syntax highlighting, fuzzy search, and mouse support.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBmantis\fR [\fB\-l\fR|\fB\-\-language\fR] [\fB\-\-completions\fR] [\fB\-\-print\-man\-page\fR] [\fB\-\-update\fR] [\fB\-\-telemetry\-status\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] [\fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A fast terminal file tree viewer — navigate filesystems, preview files with syntax highlighting, fuzzy\-search files and content, browse git history, and switch themes.
.PP
Pager mode: with no <PATH> and stdin not a terminal, mantis reads stdin instead of a directory — diff\-shaped input renders as a navigable side\-by\-side diff, anything else is syntax\-highlighted:
  git diff | mantis
  kubectl logs pod | mantis
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-language\fR \fI<LANG>\fR
Force the syntax highlighting language for piped stdin
.TP
\fB\-\-completions\fR \fI<SHELL>\fR
Generate shell completions (bash, zsh, fish, powershell)
.TP
\fB\-\-print\-man\-page\fR
Print the man page to stdout
.TP
\fB\-\-update\fR
Self\-update to the latest release
.TP
\fB\-\-telemetry\-status\fR
Print telemetry status and directory
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.TP
[\fIPATH\fR]
File or directory to open (default: current directory)
.SH VERSION
v0.16.4
